cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.IR, cs.SI. 

The paper deals with video summarisation, which is a task related to computer vision and multimedia analysis. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel unsupervised framework to learn jointly from both visual and non-visual data sources, which involves machine learning techniques and data fusion. Hence, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.MM (Multimedia) are also likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of weather reports and traffic sensory signals, which are related to information retrieval (cs.IR) and sensor networks (cs.SI), respectively.
